# Ramsey in Graph Theory

An exploration of Infinite and Finite Ramsey Theory through the lens of graph colorings. This project accompanies a web post walking through the mathematical foundations of Ramsey's theorems, including formal proofs, and their philosophical implications.

The code implements two approaches to finding Ramsey numbers: a brute force coloring search and a backtracking algorithm guided by a danger-scoring heuristic that prunes the search space. Visualizations of graph colorings are generated throughout to illustrate the search process, including an animated walkthrough of the backtracking algorithm in action.

Helper functions are defined in `utils.py` and imported into the main Jupyter notebook, which mirrors the narrative structure of the post.
